==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Palometa
<hw>Pa`lo*me"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A type of pompano (<spn>Palometa simillima</spn>) that is smaller
than the Florida pompano; it is common in West Indies. Called also the
<altname>California pompano</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> California pompano, <spn>Palometa
simillima</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>palomino</ent>⟦br⟧
